-- Popolare di Sondrio H1 net profit nearly doubles
-- 
-- Thu Aug 28, 2014 11:55AM EDT
-- None



MILAN, Aug 28 (Reuters) - Italian mid-sized lender Banca Popolare di Sondrio <BPSI.MI> said on Thursday its net profit had nearly doubled to 71 million euros ($94 million) in the first half of 2014, thanks to a sharp rise in trading income.

Popolare di Sondrio, one of 15 Italian banks under scrutiny by the European Central Bank in a health check of euro zone lenders, said its Common Equity Tier 1 ratio had risen to 9.95 percent when taking into acount a recent 343-million euro capital increase.